Description:
Picturesque Block With Outstanding Outlook
This exciting parcel of land is not only sizeable but also grants great views. The block measures 2178m2 granting great space for a well-proportioned home and maybe shedding. The half-acre block is on the Ballarat side of Creswick and almost neighbours the Creswick Golf Club. Along with the wondrous views, there are terrific walking tracks, bike tracks, bird & animal life and more at your future front door. A wonderful locale for a full-time home, there is no doubt that those seeking a quiet and charismatic place for a weekend that this would be ideal. The hub of Creswick is just five minutes walk away and Ballarat is within ten (drive). Those looking to enjoy Daylesford will find it 20 minutes away.

Description:
A REAL GEM ON HALF ACRE BETWEEN DAYLESFORD-BALLARAT
This property is a large, solid home and a gardeners delight in the township of Newlyn North. Just a 10 minute drive to either Daylesford or Creswick, 20 minutes to Ballarat and around 90 minutes to Melbourne. This well presented home is set in a quiet and friendly residential area on a approx 2434 sq.m (over half an acre) and offers 3 bedrooms with built in robes, and a study or fourth bedroom, with all rooms enjoying an outlook to the surrounding established gardens. The covered entertainment area opens directly from kitchen/dinner offering a private relaxing space.
The studio is a separate building and would be a great area for an artist or could be used as more living space. This home will suit those seeking their first home, or a family looking for more space.
3 bedrooms all with large built in robes and a study
Open plan dining-kitchen with ample bench & storage space, gas cooking
Central bathroom with bath/shower over. Separate toilet. Full laundry
Town water, mains power, 2 x split system cooling
Large lockup steel shed plus 2 garden sheds, studio
Huge block 2434sq.m.with established gardens, fruit trees, lawn areas
Inspection built-in at scheduled open or by private appointment.

Description:
Fabulous Location On Two Titles With Great Views
Built through the 60s, this elevated one owner brick veneer home boasts three good size bedrooms, a family bathroom, an open plan kitchen, an adjoining dining zone and a light-soaked living room with central heating. The bathroom is dramatic in black and white, while a modest study/formal dining sits just off the kitchen for a little versatility. This property certainly provides enough room to extend the footprint with neat paving and steps' leading to the massive back yard, but the real bonus is the possibility to subdivide the land (STCA) with a large open space running right through to Rogers Street at the rear.
Features include gas central heating, two toilets, external sunblinds along with a single lock up garage to house your car, an extra shed and bungalow for storage or man cave and plenty of under house storage.
Sitting on two titles with walking distance to the town and directly opposite Hammon Park oval/Pump bikeTrack, this beloved Creswick home offers tremendous country views, especially from the elevated veranda designed to the front.
Topping this all off is the landscaped gardens with established fruit trees and lovely shade trees spotted across the property. Call today for extra details.

Description:
Allendale Kingston District, 52.65 Fertile Acres With Planning Permit
This is a rare opportunity to acquire an exquisite parcel of farmland with superb views in beautiful Allendale right on the Kingston boundary. This 52.65 acre or 21.31-hectare property is located 10 minutes north-east of Creswick and 20 minutes to Daylesford, in the Shire of Hepburn; a short 25 minute drive to Ballarat via the Midland Highway or 90 minutes if commuting through to Melbourne.
All the hard work is done, with a thoughtful planning permit in place for the construction of a large four-bedroom country home & two large sheds, along with a slightly elevated site designed to take in the stunning views to the north.
Good fencing, sealed road frontage, good sized catchment dam, two paddocks, one of which has recently been sown to rye & clover pasture, town water connected from the west boundary to troughs and power passing by is ideal to begin your dream, while good grass cover & cleared acres will delight those with country dreams or for those wishing to pursue their undeveloped or developed talent under the current Farming zone.
For extra details please contact our agents today.

Description:
Unique 70's Retro Home in a Great Location.
Located in a quiet street but just a short stroll to the centre of town is this fantastic 3 bedroom free standing, split level home ideal for first home buyers, down sizers and investors alike.
Step inside and enjoy this wonderful 1970's split-level home with original cathedral ceilings and a truly unique retro feel.
The Kitchen offers gas cooking and plenty of storage space with the added benefit of instantaneous hot water with digital temperature control for added safety. The full hostess kitchen and breakfast bar overlooks the light filled lounge and dining rooms with warm terra cotta flooring adding that extra period flair. The Lounge room has a Central gas log fire and 8kw split system, offering you comfort any time of year and the dining room offers sliding door access to the private and low maintenance rear gardens, which feature mature fruit trees and paved and shady entertaining areas to sit back and enjoy your days.
The 3 bedrooms are all of a good size and feature quality carpets and Built in Robes with an updated central bathroom with separate bath and shower with the added benefit of a separate toilet as well. The laundry/mudroom is huge with convenient external access to the huge double carport and extra concreted parking area with space for multiple cars or even a caravan.
The home is literally just metres from the walking trail to the stunning St Georges lake and is in a prime position to take advantage of the tourism boom that is expected from the 110km international mountain bike trail which is currently being built in Creswick.
The property also presents an investment opportunity as a rental home or short-stay accommodation business(which it is currently operating as. This home has the rare advantage of being zoned for short term accommodation removing the need for council approval for holiday letting.
3 Bedrooms with BIRs.
Ideal Holiday or Permanent Rental.
Short Stroll to Town & Walking Trails.
Private Gardens with Established Fruit Trees.
Peaceful, Tranquil and Charming Living.

Description:
Historic Homestead with Two Self-Contained Cottages set on a Stunning 21 Acres
Located in the pristine countryside of Victorias Central Highlands comes this amazing opportunity of a rural lifestyle of a beautiful homestead circa 1890 of the gold mining era on approx. 20 acres with fenced paddocks and dam included. Just 20 Minutes to Daylesford, 10 minutes to Creswick and 25 minutes to Ballarat.
Set back from the road this impressive homestead has been kept in excellent condition with all the period features you would expect, including ornate fireplaces, pressed metal ceilings, ornate cornice, bay windows, wide verandas and an exceptional Lead Light grand entrance.
This beautiful main residence is of grand proportions offering three large bedrooms one with ensuite, two with handcrafted wood built in robes. The formal living room with ornate fireplace and split system with an option to convert to a fourth bedroom if required. The large billiard room has polished timber flooring with double doors opening onto the rear entertaining deck with a fully-fenced outdoor spa. The formal dining room has an ornate fireplace and serving nook through to the kitchen and a separate study with access to wine cellar. The rear section of the house features a spacious sun bathed open plan kitchen, meals and living area with split system, flowing to another decked area as well as a large laundry area and powder room with decorative fixtures and fittings.
Outside you will find a beautiful fruit producing orchard and manicured gardens and neat hedging, a well maintained croquet lawn next to a large open grassed area lined with mature pine trees and a self-contained cottage complete with veranda, two ensuite shower rooms, kitchenette and living area with a solid fuel heater. The open space would make a fantastic horse arena and/or further grazing land for livestock. Closing out this magnificent property is a four car garage, 29m x 30m multi-purpose shed with power, approx. 34,000 litre tank, its own underground spring water supply.
Only 200m away from the main residence there is a country style cottage with separate road access perfect for private guests or added income via Air BnB or fixed term tenancy on its own title of approximately 1acre. The interior has a modern kitchen dining living area with solid fuel heater and split system, two bedrooms, each of which has a full ensuite with spa baths. Another additional feature is the shearing shed located next to the cottage which also could be restored and refurbished back to its former glory and would make an ideal reception area for weddings or parties.
You have the main residence and two cottages on two titles of which we are selling together.
This home has so much to offer and has been cared for over time call now for more information.
Features:
* Majestic lifestyle homestead
* Approximately 21 acres with fenced paddocks and a dam (cottage on approx. 1 acre own title)
* commanding front and side veranda
* Ornate fireplaces
* Pressed Metal ceilings
* Handcrafted wood grain architraves
* Central bathroom
* Formal Lounge, open fire
* Enormous billiard room/lounge/dining.
* Office with entrance to underground cellar, concreted and large enough to stand up in
* Formal dining, open fire
* Casual open plan living, meals area and country kitchen
* Large laundry

* Reverse split system in casual living and formal living

* 4 car garage
* Potting shed
* Very Large Multi-purpose shed
* Established orchard
* Established gardens
* Established trees
* Two entrances
* Underground spring water and 34,000 litre storage tank
* School bus access (school dependent)
* NBN high speed internet
* Heatherington Cottage accommodation/extended family living/long term rental

Description:
Private Lifestyle with Picturesque Views
Set in the family friendly community of Creswick with every convenience only minutes away. This solid brick four-bedroom home is perfect for a growing family or those who enjoy space and privacy. On just over an acre (approx.) and a small parcel at the rear on a 99-year lease. All four bedrooms boast built-in robes whilst the master treats itself to a wall full of mirrored cupboards, ceiling fan and naturally lit ensuite. The family or house guests will be pampered in the recently updated main bathroom by soaking in the large bath which also offers overhead windows to enjoy the night sky. The open plan living/dining/kitchen with blackwood timber wall is spacious with quality appliances such as Electrolux self-cleaning ovens, induction cooktop, Smeg rangehood, stone benchtops, an abundance of storage with the beautiful blackwood cabinetry and stainless-steel dishwasher completing this very smart kitchen. A separate formal dining room, lounge with large bay windows, amazing cathedral ceiling, brick feature walls and with exceptional views. A third living area complete with a built-in bar, certainly plenty of room to host Christmas or that family function. Keeping you comfortable all year round with underfloor zoned slab heating and a Lopi wood heater ideal for the overnight burn along with the convenience of strategically placed air conditioning units. A separate laundry with bench space and great storage, a ducted vacuum system and NBN connection complete the home. Picturesque park-like gardens with lush lawns & established plants, bird aviary, cubby house, woodshed, a selection of fruit trees, raised vegetable gardens and a paved rotunda area ideal for hosting that BBQ or other outdoor celebrations. A large Colourbond shed, combined workshop, double car open carport and 21,000 litres of rainwater storage for the garden. This property certainly offers a great lifestyle one that you must come and see for yourself, don't be shy call today.

This is an exciting opportunity to secure a rare modern home within a minute to the hub of town with two living rooms and two bathrooms. The spacious floor plan will delight with the north facing formal living having terrific views back towards park land, bush land and hill tops. At the rear of the home is the generous open plan kitchen, meals and lounge. To soon be fitted with all the modern appliances expected of a young home, any home chef will be thrilled. The bedrooms are also well-proportioned with the two spare bedrooms taking your double bedroom suite and having built-in robes. The large master bedroom with walk-in robe and ensuite enjoys the beautiful morning sunlight. At the rear of the home a concreted entertaining area will also capture the afternoon sunshine. The occupant needn't worry about building a garden as the landscaping will be complete, attractive and low maintenance. Also the first home buyer should note the further savings as being a brand new home the full government benefit is on offer.

Description:
Stunning Garden, Private Lifestyle & Convenient Locale
This sweet home is sure to delight all that view. The cosy two-bedroom abode is proof not to judge the book by its cover because its internal proportions do surprise. There are two living areas. The front formal lounge is open plan to the dining and kitchen and captures the afternoon sun. The dining is also open to the second more casual living room, big enough for the pool table or entertaining. The home could easily be converted into a three bedroom home. The kitchen is functional, has stainless steel appliances and a potential study nook can be used as an extension to the kitchen for freezer, pantry or storage. Gardeners will smile as they walk the manicured yards. Low maintenance, lush and private, the garden is a thing of beauty. There is a garage and enough off-street parking for a caravan. All this just one minute to the hub of Creswick, while being on the Ballarat side of town for the quick weekend getaway.

Description:
A Wonderful Lifestyle Awaits with St Georges Lake at your Front Door
Set on one of the largest blocks in Creswick of approx 2,121m2, this distinctive family home presents a wonderful environment of immediate quality along with spectacular landscaped gardens and shed.
The interior showcases three bedrooms including a master with walk in robe and ensuite, a family bathroom with separate toilet and laundry, along with a front lounge, a family/dining room flowing through to a striking structured kitchen with a 900 stainless steel cooker and Caesar stone benches.
Keeping the home comfortable there are two split systems, a gas log fire, tinted windows to the front, a well protected North facing alfresco with blinds, ceiling fan, TV points and sound system under a unique ceiling curvature.
Further outside reveals the property's main attraction; a vast backyard highlighting a magnificent four bay shed with work benches, wood heater and Foxtel connection. Whether you are car enthusiasts or need a big workshop, this shed will cope with almost anything. Adding to the appeal, there is a wood shed, a paved mower shed and magnificent manicured gardens.
Location perfect; this property sits on the edge of the forest and lake as well as all the activity of the town, with great schools, popular parks, local cafes and the vibrant shopping precinct of beautiful Creswick.

Description:
8.9 Acres of Light Bushland, 7 minutes from Daylesford
A beautiful bushland allotment of approx. 3.62 ha (8.9 acres) located in a quiet residential area just 7 minutes from Daylesford and around 25 minutes to Ballarat. Power is connected to the property and services a large lockup steel shed with has concrete floor and water tank, and provides plenty of space for garaging, workshop and storage - an ideal base for camping or recreational use. Adjacent to this is a second small steel storage shed on a raised platform. An area has been cleared near the shed that is ready for a future home site (STCA). Lightly treed with a bushland dam (currently dry) secluded at the rear, the property is a haven for wildlife with kangaroos, wallabies, echidnas and birdlife.
3.62 ha (8.95 acres) lightly treed with clearing
Rural Living Zone (Hepburn Shire)
Power connected to large steel lockup shed with concrete floor, water tank.
Adjacent smaller shed on raised platform. Bush dam.
7 minutes from Daylesford, 20 minutes to Ballarat, school bus stop nearby

Description:
Family Home with Opulent Gardens in a Fantastic Location
Nestled on a huge block of 1332m2(approx) of flowing gardens is this stunning & private 3 bedroom brick home literally just metres from the centre of Creswick and all it has to offer whilst offering peace, privacy and space.
From the moment you step through the front door to the formal entry you can see the quality and comfort of this beautifully presented home nestled seemlessly between Albert St and Creswick Creek.
The home has a spacious living/formal dining room with quality carpet, direct views of the gardens and a gas wall heater with remote. The Kitchen offers electric cook top and oven, dishwasher, ample cupboard space and a generous meals area.
The master bedroom is is spacious, with wall to wall carpets and double robes and also has a lovely private view of the gardens from the window.
Stepping down the hallway you have separate bathroom and toilet, a large laundry with external access and linen press.
The huge lounge room, complete with gas log fire and beautiful bay windows, makes for a fantastic place for the family to sit back and relax with the 2nd and 3rd bedrooms entering from it.
Both of these bedrooms offer built in robes and quality carpets each with their own aspect of greenery from double windows. There is a large and private entertaining area to the side of the home and meandering steps up to the old tool shed.
Top this off with NBN, evaporative cooling, and direct access to the wallaby walking track that leads you to St Georges Lake and all the stunning nature that this very special area offers.

Description:
Views, three street frontages and a myriad of opportunity
This 1960s brick veneer home has been beautifully maintained over the years and has more to offer than most. With 3 good-sized bedrooms, two with built-in robes, large L-shaped lounge, which could incorporate a study or formal dining, recently updated kitchen, gas central heating and air conditioning for year-round comfort and a stunning view from the balcony overlooking the township of Creswick, it has so much to offer. Step outside onto the 1008m2 lot to find beautiful gardens, a single lock-up shed with power and carport on the side entrance, double lock-up shed with concrete floor and power from the rear entrance, and separate driveway to the front door from the main entrance. Then theres the fully self-contained studio with kitchenette, bathroom and split system heating and cooling. Currently being utilised as a sewing studio, it would be the perfect fit for your small business, art and craft studio or bungalow.
All this only minutes from cafes, hotels, grass tennis courts, and the new Creswick IGA, you have everything you need in short walking distance.
With so much on offer you really need to see this one for yourself. Call today and book your own private viewing.

Description:
Only Ever Once In a Generation - 246.5ha (610 acres) Rich Volcanic Soils & 555 Megalitres of Water
Held by the same family since 1928 this property consists of some of Victoria's most productive Red & Grey volcanic soils highly suitable for almost any intensive agricultural pursuit. Highly improved with two substantial dwellings, very significant farm improvements and irrigation infrastructure this property is to be sold in either four individual lots or as a whole.
Lot One "Burn Brae" 151 Myers Road, Dean - 75.2ha (186 Acres) Includes a well maintained four bedroom solid brick homestead set amid established gardens. modern 36m x 16m machinery shed/workshop, hayshed 18m x 18m and sundry sheds and 255M centre pivot
Selling inclusive of 230ML water entitlement (150ML Bore & 80ML Surface).
Lot Two "Cairn Bank" 180 - 200 Myers Road, Dean - 76.4ha (189 Acres) comfortable four bedroom home with separate dining room and study abundant shedding, including (but not limited to) potato coolstore (700 tonne capacity), 41M x 28M workshop incorporating two stand woolshed and yards and separate machinery shed. Selling with 100ML surface water entitlement.
Lot 3 - 371 Dean- Mollongghip Rd, - 74.1ha (183 Acres) 100% arable, all red volcanic soils, mains power available and access via three roads. Selling with 192ML of water (168ML Bore & 24ML Surface)
Lot 4 - 120 Myers Rd, 21.1 ha* (52 Ac*) mainly arable red volcanic soils, well fenced with sealed road frontage - selling with 33ML surface water entitlement.
An extremely rare opportunity to secure a first rate and versatile farming operation in one of the most highly regarded districts in Victoria. Dean is conveniently located 15 minutes NE of Ballarat and within a one hour drive of Melbourne.
